First Read: 05-Feb-26
HB386 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Elmore County; to amend Section 45-26-233,
4 Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for pistol permit
5 fees.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. Section 45-26-233, Code of Alabama 1975, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 "§45-26-233
10 (a) In Elmore County, in addition to any fee or fees
11 provided for by law there shall be an additional the issuance
12 fee for a pistol permit or license as provided for in Section
13 13A-1l-75 in the amount of shall be twenty dollars ($20).
14 (b) One dollar ($1) of each fee collected under
15 subsection (a) shall be paid into the county general fund and
16 the remaining nineteen dollars ($19) of each fee shall be
17 deposited by the sheriff of the county in any bank located in
18 the county, into a fund known as the Sheriffs' Law Enforcement
19 Fund. The fund shall be drawn upon by the sheriff or duly
20 authorized agent and shall be used exclusively for law
21 enforcement purposes.
22 (c) The establishment of the Sheriffs' Law Enforcement
23 Fund as provided in this section and the use of such the fund
24 shall in no way diminish or take the place of any other
25 imbursement or other source of income established for the
26 sheriff or the operation of his or her office."
27 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
28 1, 2026.
